overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification. I performed an in-depth
  analysis of the codebase, covering data models, API endpoints, admin
  functionalities, and all questionnaire sections. This review led to the
  creation of a structured plan, highlighting both well-implemented features and
  critical gaps, categorized by priority. Following the user's approval, I began
  implementing the plan. The first major task, integrating a 1-10 tiredness
  severity scale with crucial safety warnings, has been successfully completed
  across the application's data types, validation, user interface, and both web
  and PDF report generation. Additionally, the detection logic for Comorbid
  Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) has been added, marking progress on another
  high-priority item.
